    "bodyText": "<p><iframe width=\"700\" height=\"394\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/wXm7vgmP_c0?fs=1&amp;feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"\"></iframe></p>\n<p>“The Portland crew loaded up at 2:30 am  from Rip City Skate and set off for 7 days with 7 passengers for the  epic hills of Santa Barbara and San Francisco, and everything in  between. The trip was a huge success, the newly upgraded bus ran  flawlessly, at times with over 30 riders climbing up hills.  Here’s a  little evidence from the journey!”</p>\n<p>The SkateHouse crew meet up with the bus in Santa Barbara for some runs. We’re editing down the footage now so expect an edit shortly.</p>",
