    "pageTitle": "Caliber Truck Co.- Double Dutch Bus Tour",
    "postDate": "2011-05-31",
    "author": "SkateHouseMedia",
    "bodyText": "<p><iframe src=\"//player.vimeo.com/video/83705939?title=0&amp;byline=0&amp;color=9e0000\" height=\"394\" width=\"700\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe></p>\n<p>Every winter, skaters migrate to warmer climates to get more skating in during the year. The skate crews based in Cascadia have organized a large excursion deep into SoCal for the past three years. This year, a crew of 40+ skaters packed the Sunset Slider bus and the PDX bus chased the warm weather South, dubbing the trip “The Double Dutch Bus Tour.” – <a href=\"https://calibertruckco.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Caliber Truck Co.</a></p>",
