    "pageTitle": "Event Coverage: Angelopolis Outlaw",
    "postDate": "January 15, 2016",
    "author": "SkateHouseMedia",
    "bodyText": "<p>Down in Colombia, a few dozen locals gathered together for an Outlaw Race on a narrow ridge run on the outskirts of Medellin. No prize money, no free gear, just traffic, narrow runs, and bragging rights. In the end <a href=\"https://s1helmets.com\">S1</a> and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://valhallaskateboards.com\">Valhalla</a>‘s&nbsp;Team of Bad Bitches swept the podium.</p>\n<p>1st Place: Francis Cooper Darquea Mauro (<a href=\"https://valhallaskateboards.com\">Valhalla’s</a>, <a href=\"https://s1helmets.com\">S1</a>, <a href=\"https://calibertruckco.com\" target=\"_blank\">Caliber</a>, <a href=\"https://arborcollective.com/skateboards/products/wheels/\" target=\"_blank\">Sucrose</a>)</p>\n<p>2nd Place: Santiago Granada (<a href=\"https://valhallaskateboards.com\">Valhalla’s</a>, <a href=\"https://s1helmets.com\">S1</a>)</p>\n<p>3rd Place: Juan Pablo Villegas (<a href=\"https://www.gullwingtruckco.com\" target=\"_blank\">Gullwing</a>, <a href=\"https://s1helmets.com\">S1</a>)</p>\n<p>4th Place: Felipe Marin (<a href=\"https://valhallaskateboards.com\">Valhalla’s</a>, <a href=\"https://s1helmets.com\">S1</a>)</p>",
