    "pageTitle": "Skatesgiving: East Coast Corner Session",
    "postDate": "2015-12-09",
    "author": "SkateHouseMedia",
    "bodyText": "<p><iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/57585494\" width=\"700\" height=\"394\" frameborder=\"0\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" allowfullscreen=\"\"></iframe></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.skatehousemedia.com/tags/skatesgiving\">Skatesgiving</a>‘s ode to east coast downhill skateboarding. For the most part, the right coast’s mountain passes &amp; canyons runs are scarce. Most kids will find the best corner they have and hit it over &amp; over. Here is our ode to that classic corner hike. Brought to you in part by: <a href=\"https://www.cometskateboards.com/home/\" target=\"_blank\">Comet</a>, <a href=\"https://www.sector9.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Sector 9</a>, <a href=\"https://www.landyachtz.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Landyachtz</a>, &amp; Kebbek.</p>\n<p><b><span id=\"more-7967\"></span></b></p>\n<p><iframe width=\"700\" height=\"394\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/JyoqV064nx8\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"\"></iframe></p>",
