    "pageTitle": "Sessions: Salt Lake City  | SkateHouseMedia.com",
    "postDate": "2012-06-10",
    "author": "SkateHouseMedia",
    "bodyText": "<p>    <iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/36126810\" width=\"700\" height=\"394\" frameborder=\"0\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" allowfullscreen=\"\"></iframe></p>\n<p>Believe it or not Salt Lake City has a booming longboard scene. Its been growing for a long time and now has no room for hibernation.  The city has everything you need as a skater. We got to take train rides to the top of town, sick mountains surrounding salt lake, and a crew of rippers the know all the spots. Rad skate city, just don’t visit in winter like we did.</p>\n<p>Also Check out Micah Green’s blog- <a href=\"https://slutcityskating.blogspot.com/2012/02/fbgm-campus-massacre-2012.html\">Salt Lurk City</a></p>\n<p>Special thanks to Marc McCrudden for making the trip possible to watch ‘<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ozd6yRcIM1g\" target=\"_blank\">Drop</a>‘ show at the 2012 X-Dance Film Festival</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.skatehousemedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/drop.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-4774\" title=\"drop\" src=\"https://www.skatehousemedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/drop-700x522.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"700\" height=\"522\"></a></p>",
