    "pageTitle": "La Teta",
    "postDate": "February 16, 2016",
    "author": "SkateHouseMedia",
    "bodyText": "<p>La Teta (The Tit) is one of the steepest roads you will ever find. Most cars can barely make it up this thing, let alone a car full of skaters and gear. Alex had Axel Serrat, Cooper Darquea (<a href=\"https://valhallaskateboards.com\">Valhalla</a>, <a href=\"https://s1helmets.com\">S1</a>, <a href=\"https://arborcollective.com\">Sucrose</a>, <a href=\"https://calibertruckco.com\">Caliber</a>), and Felipe Marin (<a href=\"https://valhallaskateboards.com\">Valhalla</a>, <a href=\"https://s1helmets.com\">S1</a>) push the follow car up the hill so we could do a bit of filming. Watch Axel pray for the brick with his freakishly slidey wheels trying not to hit the barbed wire fence that wraps along the entire outside of the run.</p>",
