    "pageTitle": "Skatesgiving: The South | SkateHouseMedia.com",
    "postDate": "2015-01-15",
    "author": "SkateHouseMedia",
    "bodyText": "<p>    <iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/37422041\" width=\"700\" height=\"394\" frameborder=\"0\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" allowfullscreen=\"\"></iframe></p>\n<p>Go take a gaze at the sponsors’ websites that made <a href=\"../tag/skatesgiving\">Skatesgiving</a> possible: <a href=\"https://www.cometskateboards.com/home/\">Comet</a>, Kebbek, <a href=\"https://landyachtz.com/\">Lanyachtz</a>, <a href=\"https://sector9.com/\">Sector 9</a>, Rotule, &amp; <a href=\"https://www.raynelongboards.com/\">Rayne.</a></p>\n<p>It’s both thanks to them and the filmers that this trip was feasible. Those cameramen were <a href=\"https://mclovinmyliferightnow.wordpress.com/\">Matt Livingston</a>, <a href=\"https://www.skatehousemedia.com/tags/matt-kienzle\">Matt K</a> &amp; Olivier Séguin-Leduc over at <a href=\"https://teamquebec.org/\">Team Quebec</a>. Housemate <a href=\"https://www.skatehousemedia.com/tags/max-dubler\">Max Dubler</a> also came on the trip and took pictures for the newest <a href=\"https://www.skateslate.com/subscriptions-longboarding-magazine/\">Skateslate</a> magazine.</p>",
