    "pageTitle": "Locals: Max Ballesteros",
    "postDate": "2017-03-03",
    "author": "SkateHouseMedia",
    "bodyText": "<p>San Diego <a href=\"https://skatehousemedia.com/category/locals\" target=\"_blank\">Local</a> Max Ballesteros is a well known name in the downhill skateboarding scene. He’s been all over the world attending races and even rounded out the podium on <a href=\"https://skatehousemedia.com/category/locals\" target=\"_blank\">IDF</a> world rankings last year. Max met up with <a href=\"https://skatehousemedia.com/tags/matt-kienzle\" target=\"_blank\">Matt K</a> to find a dry road in the golden state during a period of non stop rain, check out what they were able to garner. Ballesteros rides Bustin boards, Ronin trucks, <a href=\"https://www.radesigns.com\" target=\"_blank\">RAD wheels</a>, <a href=\"https://www.muirskate.com\" target=\"_blank\">Muirskate</a>, Hondar, Atopic, &amp; Vultur.</p>",
