    "pageTitle": "Descending from 9000 with Muir Skate",
    "postDate": "2013-01-25",
    "author": "SkateHouseMedia",
    "bodyText": "<p><iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/YuM9CFSoDU4?rel=0\" height=\"394\" width=\"700\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe></p>\n<p>Got to love Muir! They pile the crew in the van and take them to epic places to skate!</p>\n<p>“This winter, MuirSkate headed out to some of the gnarliest hills on the West Coast, with a few friends. Starting at 9000 feet, we descended down the mountain, pushing our skills to its limit. Wheels were thrashed and skin was lost, but it was definitely a weekend to remember. We’ll definitely be back…” – <a href=\"https://www.muirskate.com\">Muir Skate</a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
