    "pageTitle": "Rayne Team Rider: George Mackenzie",
    "postDate": "2012-08-15",
    "author": "SkateHouseMedia",
    "bodyText": "<p><iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/xqrb1wH9Cvc?rel=0\" height=\"394\" width=\"700\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe></p>\n<p>“About a year ago, George Mackenzie visited <a href=\"https://www.RayneLongboards.com\" target=\"_blank\">Rayne</a> to grab some Vicious, we asked him what he was up to and he said: “It’s Complicated”. We’d go for coffee now and then and chat, but not much came of it, we figured we were “Just Friends”. George was skating for the sake of skating and that was okay. Then one day we were hanging out by a bowl, George was doing his thing and then all of a sudden he came over, sat down beside us and said, “Will you?” We said “YES!” And now we’re in a relationship. Love you George! Welcome to the Family.”</p>",
