    "pageTitle": "Raw Run: Split The Difference",
    "postDate": "April 24, 2015",
    "author": "SkateHouseMedia",
    "bodyText": "<p><iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/125630709\" width=\"700\" height=\"394\" frameborder=\"0\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" allowfullscreen=\"\"></iframe></p>\n<p>A fun part of riding for a company is prototyping. Most of the time you get to test fun new shapes or different urethanes that sometimes never get to see the light of day. The worst part is filling out the review forms. Instead of completing the forms for <a href=\"https://skatehousemedia.com/tags/josh-rolf\">Josh Rolf</a> (Head of R&amp;D at  <a href=\"https://www.sector9.com\" target=\"_blank\">Sector 9</a>) Matt &amp; Micah sent this footage instead. <a href=\"https://skatehousemedia.com/tags/micah-green\">Micah Green</a> &amp; <a href=\"https://skatehousemedia.com/tags/matt-kienzle\">Matt Kienzle</a> packed up there stuff last summer and hit the road for the <a href=\"https://skatehousemedia.com/04/13/2015/road-trip-sector-9-kebbek-in-europe\">eurotour</a>.</p>",
