    "pageTitle": "Facetime with Martin Siegrist",
    "postDate": "2016-03-16",
    "author": "SkateHouseMedia",
    "bodyText": "<p><iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/11846805\" width=\"700\" height=\"394\" frameborder=\"0\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" allowfullscreen=\"\"></iframe></p>\n<p>The SkateHouse was stoked to have the 2004, 2006, and 2007 Downhill  Skateboarding World Champion Martin Siegrist as a guest. At races he is a  fierce and determined competitor, but outside the race scene he is a  fun, laid back, easygoing guy.</p>\n<p>Ever wonder what happened at Maryhill 2007 between K-Rimes and Martin that lead to a punch? Watch to find out.</p>\n<p>Martin is currently working and exploring hills in Malaysia, looks like he is finding some good <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jmIulUmc2Ds\" target=\"_blank\">runs</a>!  Be sure to check out his <a href=\"https://www.mrtn.ch/\" target=\"_blank\">website</a> and <a href=\"https://www.mrtn.ch/10_cali_van.html\" target=\"_blank\">writeup</a> on his trip from SkateHouse LA to Vancouver for the Drop premier.</p>",
