    "pageTitle": "Raw Run: Footage of the Footage",
    "postDate": "2012-08-14",
    "author": "SkateHouseMedia",
    "bodyText": "<p><iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/42427060?title=0&amp;byline=0&amp;color=9e0000\" width=\"700\" height=\"394\" frameborder=\"0\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" allowfullscreen=\"\"></iframe>\n</p><p>Some people have wondered how we collect our on-board footage. With a scorpion cam, dslr camera, and a fish eye, it’s as simple as riding down the hill. As always it’s safety first. Filming doesn’t give you the ability to take risky lines. </p>\n<p>Follow along for a run as housemate, Louis Pilloni, films <a href=\"https://raynelongboards.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Rayne</a> riders, Mike Slota and Aidan Lynds, captured from the GoPro on Aidan’s head. Edited footage from the run can be seen <a href=\"https://www.skatehousemedia.com/04/02/2012/visitors-aidan-lynds-and-mike-slota\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>. </p>",
