    "pageTitle": "Event: Atomic Bomb | SkateHouseMedia.com",
    "postDate": "2014-05-28",
    "author": "SkateHouseMedia",
    "bodyText": "<p><iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/24305319\" width=\"700\" height=\"394\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe></p>\n<p>The Atomic Bomb in Los Alamos, New Mexico is a fast 55mph sweeping race course challenging riders to fight to stay in their tuck. With soft gooey tar snakes running throughout the course racers had to fight wobbles beside 3 other riders as they went down. Special thanks to <a href=\"https://www.timeshipracing.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Timeship Racing</a> for hosting the event.</p>\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Results:</strong></span><br>\n1st: Zak Maytum<br>\n2nd: James Kelly<br>\n3rd: Joel Putrah<br>\n4th: Kyle Martin</p>",
