    "author": "SkateHouseMedia",
    "bodyText": "<p><iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/12480546\" width=\"700\" height=\"394\" frameborder=\"0\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" allowfullscreen=\"\"></iframe></p>\n<p>In the 60s and 70s, skaters rode drainage ditches and pipes to take  advantage of the “natural” terrain that already existed all around them.   Finding a good fullpipe to skate can be tough, which is perhaps why  this one has decades of history to it.  Join Andrew Mercado as he surfs  the endless concrete wave, brah!</p>",
