    "postDate": "2016-02-16",
    "author": "SkateHouseMedia",
    "bodyText": "<p><a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/maxwellstoreydubler/5870508416/sizes/l/in/photostream/\"><img class=\"alignnone\" title=\"Pete 21st Birthday.\" src=\"https://assets.skatehousemedia.com/post-photos/pete-eubank-skatehousemediacom/5870508416_2bd9551d69_b.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" height=\"819\"></a></p>\n<p>Madrid and Venom rider Pete Eubank celebrated his 21st birthday last Saturday by skating this beautiful spot underneath the Pacific Coast Highway in Big Sur. Later that night, he found himself trapped in a tent, unable to find the exit. Disaster was narrowly avoided when a sympathetic camper heard his calls for help and came to his rescue. Max Dubler photo.</p>",
