    "pageTitle": "Event: Kelowna Skylands 2011 | SkateHouseMedia.com",
    "postDate": "2012-09-28",
    "author": "SkateHouseMedia",
    "bodyText": "<p><iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/25752311\" width=\"700\" height=\"394\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe></p>\n<p>“Nestled on Lake Okanagan, the city of Kelowna has a new appetite for downhill skateboarding. The goal of the Kelowna DH is to provide a fun and safe environment to skate while building awareness of the skateboard community. This pristine pavement has 12 corners, including one hairpin, two at 90 degrees and chicanes filled with drafting straights and technical speed. Racers will drop 1,000 vertical feet, over a 2.5 km course, with three highly dangerous technical hairpins totaling six hay bale-exploding corners. ”</p>\n<p><strong>Results:</strong><br>\n<strong>1st</strong> – James Kelly<br>\n<strong>2nd</strong> – Andrew Chapman<br>\n<strong>3rd</strong> – George Mackenzie<br>\n<strong>4th</strong> – Brendan Davidson</p>",
