    "bodyText": "<p><iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/kgoAG6ChZFk?rel=0\" width=\"700\" height=\"394\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\n<p>“The <a href=\"https://rdvxgriptape.com/\" target=\"_blank\">RDVX</a> Grip Crew traveled to California for a good old fashion skate trip hitting gnarly hills and fast runs. Photographer, Christopher Vanderyajt, was behind the lens capturing all the locations, skating, hanging out, and of course the California sunsets. Chris captured Team Riders, Louis Pilloni, Brett Ciabattini, Axel Serrat, Jimmy Riha, and Daniel Luna. The crew hits Skate House, Santa Barbra to crash at the Orchid pushing through the cold, rainy, foggy conditions to get the trip going, and ended the trip in San Diego. See the adventure through photographs.”</p>",
