    "pageTitle": "Flashback: Rolling With Dubes | SkateHouseMedia.com",
    "postDate": "2016-07-22",
    "author": "SkateHouseMedia",
    "bodyText": "<p><iframe width=\"700\" height=\"394\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/cXstQQnxlAY\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"\"></iframe></p>\n<p>Before the SkateHouse was “the SkateHouse,” it was a quiet place home to three skaters: James Kelly, Louis Pilloni, and Brent “Dubes” Dubendorff.&nbsp; Dubes’s style is to go fast.&nbsp; Skateboards, motorcycles, anything that goes fast: he’s probably into it.</p>\n<p>Louie filmed this video of Dubes shredding a very familiar run two years ago, getting rad wearing nothing but board-shorts.&nbsp; Does he pay for it in the end?&nbsp; Let’s just say… you’re just going to have to watch to find out!</p>\n<p>Big shout out to Dubes – without him the SkateHouse wouldn’t be what it is today!&nbsp; Dubes reps <a href=\"https://www.paristruckco.com\" target=\"_blank\">Paris Truck Co</a> and Divine Wheels</p>",
