    "pageTitle": "Caliber Truck Co: The Whistler Road Trip",
    "postDate": "2013-07-21",
    "author": "SkateHouseMedia",
    "bodyText": "<p><iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/71133434?title=0&amp;byline=0&amp;portrait=0&amp;color=9e0000\" height=\"394\" width=\"700\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe></p>\n<p>2,000 miles of road covered, two crews, and two buses. The <a href=\"https://calibertruckco.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Caliber</a> and <a href=\"https://www.arborcollective.com\" target=\"_blank\">Arbor</a> teams caravanned up the coast of the Pacific Northwest skating anything and everything in their path while on their way to the Whistler Longboard Festival. Experience these two videos, captured from the different perspectives of their respective crews, and enjoy the ride of an epic skate trip without having to deal with the smells of a bus packed with skaters who haven’t showered in two weeks.</p>",
