    "postDate": "2016-07-05",
    "author": "SkateHouseMedia",
    "bodyText": "<p><a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/maxwellstoreydubler/6015227943/sizes/l/in/photostream/\"><img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://assets.skatehousemedia.com/post-photos/more-giants-head/6015227943_3c916911de_b.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" height=\"1024\"></a></p>\n<p>Brian “King Brian” Elderkin has awesome standup big man style.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/maxwellstoreydubler/6015778772/sizes/l/in/photostream/\"><img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://assets.skatehousemedia.com/post-photos/more-giants-head/6015778772_0793df42aa_b.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" height=\"819\"></a></p>\n<p>Skeet skeet bang bang. Billy Bones.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/maxwellstoreydubler/6015780494/sizes/l/in/photostream/\"><img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://assets.skatehousemedia.com/post-photos/more-giants-head/6015780494_72bbfb536d_b.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" height=\"819\"></a></p>\n<p>Tom “Meatball” Edstrand designed the Evo, co-founded Landyachtz, and was world champion in ’05. He’s still shredding.</p>\n<p>Prince Dillon and JimZ after the jump.</p>\n<p><span id=\"more-3117\"></span><a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/maxwellstoreydubler/6015781012/sizes/l/in/photostream/\"><img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://assets.skatehousemedia.com/post-photos/more-giants-head/6015781012_01b7a056ff_b.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></p>\n<p>Dillon Stephens grew up in Summerland and has Giant’s Head pretty dialed. This is him winning the race on Monday.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/maxwellstoreydubler/6015278253/sizes/l/in/photostream/\"><img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://assets.skatehousemedia.com/post-photos/more-giants-head/6015278253_8184c56644_b.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" height=\"683\"></a></p>\n<p>JimZ is an original hands-down style guy. He hasn’t changed.</p>",
