    "pageTitle": "Daniel Fissmer | SkateHouseMedia.com",
    "postDate": "2015-10-02",
    "author": "SkateHouseMedia",
    "bodyText": "<p><a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/maxwellstoreydubler/6030935033/sizes/l/in/photostream/\"><img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://assets.skatehousemedia.com/post-photos/daniel-fissmer-skatehousemediacom/6030935033_a920d2aec3_b.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" height=\"683\"></a></p>\n<p>I’ve been wanting to make a toeside version of <a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/maxwellstoreydubler/4266704971/sizes/l/\" target=\"_blank\">this photo</a> for a while; but didn’t know anyone who had switch toeside checks dialed. Enter Daniel Fissmer, an up-and-coming East Coast shredder who’s been chilling in California for the summer. Dude’s got ‘em every try and didn’t even need to warm up and get used to the sketchy pavement. Look out for this kid. – Max.</p>",
