    "author": "SkateHouseMedia",
    "bodyText": "<p><iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/27499081\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe></p>\n<p>Just because the daylight hours are gone doesn’t mean skate sessions have to stop.</p>\n<p>“Hey Skatehouse! Hope you guys are ripping and shredding. My name’s Dhiya, from the teeny tiny sunny island of Singapore. We don’t have big mountains and hills in Singapore and it’s definitely not legal to skate on most of the roads here, the government’s pretty uptight on these kinda things (in simpler terms BIT*H A*SS GOVERNMENT) but that hasn’t stop us from skating. Lately the scene has exploded beyond imagination, i’ve been learning how to shoot and edit vids recently to document my boys shredding. Cheers!” – Dhiya Muhammad</p>",
