    "pageTitle": "Angie’s Curves 2014 – Teaser",
    "postDate": "2013-06-20",
    "author": "SkateHouseMedia",
    "bodyText": "<p><iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/M6QqW-GW0yM?rel=0\" width=\"700\" height=\"394\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\n<p>“<a href=\"https://www.angiescurves.com\" target=\"_blank\">Angie’s Curves</a>, located in Pala, California, is one of the most challenging downhill races on the World Cup Circuit. Nine harrowing turns, over 1.34 miles, and speeds upwards of 70mph put the world’s best downhill skateboarders to test. It is the 7th stop on the 2014 IDF (International Downhill Federation) World Cup Series. The event will be broadcast live utilizing 8 live feed cameras to capture the action. Tune in on Sept 13th &amp; 14th to WATCH IT LIVE!!!”</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.internationaldownhillfederation.org/page/angies-curves-registration\" target=\"_blank\">Sign up to Race</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.internationaldownhillfederation.org/page/volunteer-to-work-at-angies-curves-2014\" target=\"_blank\">Sign up to Volunteer </a></p>",
