    "pageTitle": "Rayne: Levi Green – Prototyping the Rayne Darkside",
    "postDate": "2016-01-16",
    "author": "SkateHouseMedia",
    "bodyText": "<p><iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/Qvq7a0_X4sw?rel=0\" height=\"394\" width=\"700\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe></p>\n<p>“<a href=\"https://www.raynelongboards.com/team\" target=\"_blank\">Rayne Team Rider Levi Green</a> is well known for mad steez, redrilling everything and Purple. We figured we could combine these traits with Levi’s ability to skate everything to prototype a new board for the Summer 2013 line-up we thought he would like – the Rayne Darkside. How much do you know about <a href=\"https://www.RayneLongboards.com\" target=\"_blank\">Rayne</a> proto’s?… The Darkside is a Directional, Top Mount Freeride board with Radial Drop, Rocker and a Kick-tail. The Darkside has a short wheelbase, narrower width and just enough flare to put on some 70mm Rayne Envy Wheels, but we think it’s most fun on the 62mm Envy. Come over to the Darkside!”</p>",
