    "pageTitle": "Comet Skateboards // Tim Smith on the Ethos ‘BP’ 34",
    "postDate": "2012-06-12",
    "author": "SkateHouseMedia",
    "bodyText": "<p><iframe width=\"700\" height=\"394\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/9hSETdwq3qs?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"\"></iframe></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.cometskateboards.com\" target=\"_blank\">Comet Skateboards</a> is proud to present <a href=\"https://www.skatehousemedia.com/tags/tim-smith\">Tim Smith</a> skating the newest size of the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://store.cometskateboards.com/ethos-34/\" target=\"_blank\">Ethos 34</a>.</p>\n<p>Tim Smith is one of the newest to be joining up on the Comet Team. Hailing from small town Ontario Tim Smith embodies the skate it all mentality we love so much here at Comet. Tim does it all with a unique relaxed style we cant help but dig. In this video Tim puts the Ethos 34 through its paces on every type of terrain, including some heavy DH. This board can do it all!</p>\n<p>The newest smallest board in our long time favourite Ethos series. This board was designed and tested by <a href=\"https://www.skatehousemedia.com/tags/brian-peck\">Brian Peck</a> and made perfect for all your path skating, park skating, freeride and downhill needs.</p>\n<p>The Ethos 34 has already shipped to select stores! Check your local shop for one now.</p>",
