    "postDate": "2011-08-16",
    "author": "SkateHouseMedia",
    "bodyText": "<p><iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/28732603\" width=\"700\" height=\"394\" frameborder=\"0\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" allowfullscreen=\"\"></iframe></p>\n<p>“Giants Head Freeride is a downhill skateboarding event situated in the  beautiful Okanagan Valley of British Columbia, Canada. This years event  took place on July 30th, 31st and August 1st, 2011 (BC Day long  weekend) at Giant’s Head Park in Summerland BC. With over 100  riders for this epic three day freeride and a head to  head race on Monday afternoon all riders left satisfied. The course consists of 13 expert level hairpin corners and 700  vertical feet of drop, which sends riders through 2.1 km of intense  riding. The event is like non other in North America – come be apart of  the fun!”</p>\n<p>Special thanks to Andrew Monaghan for organizing the event and <a href=\"https://landyachtz.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Landyachtz</a> for being the title sponsor.</p>\n<p>Music: Helena Beat – Foster the People</p>",
    "tags": [],
    "categories": [
      "Event Coverage"
    ],
    "contentUrls": [
      "https://landyachtz.com",
      "https://player.vimeo.com/video/28732603"
    ],
