    "pageTitle": "Racing Down Pikes Peak 2013",
    "postDate": "2011-01-13",
    "author": "SkateHouseMedia",
    "bodyText": "<p><iframe width=\"700\" height=\"525\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/zc8xL8-6lsk?rel=0\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"\"></iframe></p>\n<p>“America’s Mountain is famous for racing up to over 14,000 ft. The freshly paved road up to Pikes Peak gave us the perfect opportunity to spend the weekend in the Rocky Mountains for a weekend of high altitude racing. Down! Perfect weather, a twisty technical course and the best racers in the world made for some great action. We set up the TimeShip Speed Trap and clocked riders coming into the fastest corner at over 52 mph, some didn’t make that corner! Big ups to Connor Welles for putting on a world class event and to all of the sponsors that helped to make it happen.” -Timeship Racing</p>",
