    "postDate": "2012-12-27",
    "author": "SkateHouseMedia",
    "bodyText": "<p><iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/DYgNzuTIRD0?rel=0\" height=\"525\" width=\"700\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe></p>\n<p>Faster, rougher, and scarier then your typical downhill run, Soldiers of Downhill in Bainbridge, Ohio pushes riders to the edge. This race track is better then any roller coaster you have ridden. Follow down with <a href=\"https://www.landyachtz.com/D510.cfm\" target=\"_blank\">Max Wipperman</a> as he takes a run with <a href=\"https://www.skatehousemedia.com/?s=aaron+hampshire\" target=\"_blank\">Aaron Hamphire</a>, <a href=\"https://www.skatehousemedia.com/?s=Josh+Rolf\" target=\"_blank\">Josh Rolf</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/RiderApprovedDesigns\" target=\"_blank\">Louis Pilloni</a> during the first day of riding.</p>\n<p><strong>Results:</strong><br>\n1st: George Mackenzie<br>\n2nd: Max Wipperman<br>\n3rd: Matthew Kienzle<br>\n4th: Louis Pilloni</p>",
