    "author": "SkateHouseMedia",
    "bodyText": "<p><a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/maxwellstoreydubler/5083865675/sizes/l/in/photostream/\"><img src=\"https://assets.skatehousemedia.com/post-photos/some-photos/5083865675_921182617d_b.jpg\"></a><br>K-Rimes boosts a slightly blurry early grab off a weirdly-shaped bump in Malibu.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/maxwellstoreydubler/5083866605/sizes/l/in/photostream/\"><img src=\"https://assets.skatehousemedia.com/post-photos/some-photos/5083866605_1b0c732e71_b.jpg\"></a><br>Ryan started Ladera skateboards out of his parents’ basement because he wanted something to ride on the steep, twisting hills of Santa Cruz county. I’m told he’s been sessioning this hairpin for years.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/maxwellstoreydubler/5072477687/sizes/l/in/photostream/\"><img src=\"https://assets.skatehousemedia.com/post-photos/some-photos/5072477687_0f4f7c0620_b.jpg\"></a><br>Zak Maytum brought a couple local Colorado guys out to California last weekend to hit some skateparks and the Morro Bay boardercross event. This park had a full time pad nanny; but that didn’t stop Max from <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fmBd00-UvUo\">getting hurt in the parking lot</a>.</p>",
