    "pageTitle": "The Scorcher 2 | SkateHouseMedia.com",
    "postDate": "2014-08-08",
    "author": "SkateHouseMedia",
    "bodyText": "<div id=\"attachment_3776\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\" style=\"width: 710px\"><a href=\"https://www.skatehousemedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/ethanhawiidownhill.jpg\"><img src=\"https://www.skatehousemedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/ethanhawiidownhill-700x466.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"ethanhawiidownhill\" width=\"700\" height=\"466\" class=\"size-large wp-image-3776\"></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">The Finals</p></div>\n<p>“On October 15, the second event in the Hawaii  Winter Outlaw Series the Scorcher 2 went down. This event was on a  gnarly closed road going up to a water tower. The course was relatively  short, less than a quarter mile but the road was full of cracks,  gravel, big rocks, small rocks, glass, rusty metal, dead trees, and a  bunch of other things that you wouldn’t want to fall in, and to top it  all off at the fastest part of the course there is a full 180* hairpin.” – Andrew Shoji</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.skatehousemedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/hawiidownhill.jpg\"><img src=\"https://www.skatehousemedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/hawiidownhill-700x466.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"hawiidownhill\" width=\"700\" height=\"466\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-3779\"></a></p>\n<p>Above- Kj Nakanelua throws down a fat frontside check</p>\n<p>Race Recap video- The Scorcher 2 </p>\n<p>1st- Ethan Lau<br>\n2nd- Keola Chu<br>\n3rd- Eric Sato</p>\n<p><iframe width=\"700\" height=\"389\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/Jog7i4NHGDY\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"\"></iframe></p>",
