    "pageTitle": "Fan Submitted Photos",
    "postDate": "2014-07-19",
    "author": "SkateHouseMedia",
    "bodyText": "<p>We’ve been getting tons of sick pictures in the mail lately. Most of ‘em are getting pasted up on the wall as part of a photo-collage; but we’re keeping the really good ones to frame. These are the finest of the last batch…</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/maxwellstoreydubler/5092160219/sizes/l/\"><img src=\"https://assets.skatehousemedia.com/post-photos/fan-submitted-photos/5092160219_e695de86aa_b.jpg\"></a><br>Today’s background is a skate toolbox art object given to us by Skip from Portland. Skip’s a down-ass older skater and woodworker who has an epic sticker collection and makes all kinds of beautiful, sometimes very useful things for skateboarders in his garage.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/maxwellstoreydubler/5092158419/sizes/l/in/photostream/\"><img src=\"https://assets.skatehousemedia.com/post-photos/fan-submitted-photos/5092158419_8f1475702a_b.jpg\"></a><br>This quality black and white self-portrait comes to us from <s>Eric Dunmil</s> Eric Duminil, a French guy living in Stuttgart Germany. Note the steezed caveman and excellent use of a wireless camera remote. <i>(Spelling corrected. Sorry Eric! – Max)</i></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/maxwellstoreydubler/5092753098/sizes/l/in/photostream/\"><img src=\"https://assets.skatehousemedia.com/post-photos/fan-submitted-photos/5092753098_facd84c7ec_b.jpg\"></a><br>Grayson in Portland, OR sent this color print. I’m feeling the color scheme, panning, and vignetting. <b>UPDATE:</b> I’m told this shot is of Micah B.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/maxwellstoreydubler/5092155363/sizes/l/in/photostream/\"><img src=\"https://assets.skatehousemedia.com/post-photos/fan-submitted-photos/5092155363_f1cb20d3f2_b.jpg\"></a><br>Mael from France passed along this creatively-framed snap. <b>UPDATE:</b> More shots from this session <a href=\"https://williambaudouin.blogspot.com/2010/09/session-longboard.html\">here</a>.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/maxwellstoreydubler/5092153999/sizes/l/in/photostream/\"><img src=\"https://assets.skatehousemedia.com/post-photos/fan-submitted-photos/5092153999_f9192b00d5_b.jpg\"></a><br>\nJake in Larchmont, NY sent us this epic letter. Wish we could help with the homework; but we forgot all that science stuff years ago. I asked Switzer to do it ’cause he’s in engineering school; but he wanted to go skating instead.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/maxwellstoreydubler/5092749236/sizes/l/in/photostream/\"><img src=\"https://assets.skatehousemedia.com/post-photos/fan-submitted-photos/5092749236_5044bbd256_b.jpg\"></a><br><a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/maxwellstoreydubler/5092149427/sizes/l/in/photostream/\"><img src=\"https://assets.skatehousemedia.com/post-photos/fan-submitted-photos/5092149427_a1f0589fb7_b.jpg\"></a><br>Cheman from AZ snapped, printed, matted, and mailed in these sick shots of his friends Cole Kurtz and Tyler Meester. Cole has been to the SkateHouse a few times and always brings an unshakable positive attitude and several cases of Red Bull. Tyler came out and took some runs with us earlier this year. Both kids can handle their business on the board. Arizona’s been going off lately. Check out <a href=\"https://www.lifeofincondite.com/\">The Life of lncondite</a> for the latest photos and video of all the rippers out there.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/maxwellstoreydubler/5092151685/sizes/l/\"><img src=\"https://assets.skatehousemedia.com/post-photos/fan-submitted-photos/5092151685_bbf660a7ff_b.jpg\"></a><br>BOOM. Evan I from Hawaii keeps it short.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/maxwellstoreydubler/5092746940/sizes/l/\"><img src=\"https://assets.skatehousemedia.com/post-photos/fan-submitted-photos/5092746940_af4cc58f0b_b.jpg\"></a><br>This photo is sick; but unfortunately I lost the envelope it came in. If this is you, get in touch so we can put your name up. <b>UPDATE:</b> A helpful flickr commenter identified this as a shot of Trevor H by Grayson from Portland.</p>\n<p>Keep ‘em coming – Max.</p>",
    "tags": [],
    "categories": [
      "Photos"
    ],
