    "pageTitle": "Return To Radelaide",
    "postDate": "2011-07-03",
    "author": "SkateHouseMedia",
    "bodyText": "<p><iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/16119020\" width=\"700\" height=\"394\" frameborder=\"0\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" allowfullscreen=\"\"></iframe></p>\n<p>Adelaide, South Australia is now known as one of the country’s best  hot spots for downhill skateboarding. (R)Adelaide has started to draw  riders from across the nation to hang out, shred and progress their  skills on some of the most fun and challenging hills the country has to  offer. In 2010 Sydney riders joined crew from Queensland and locals  Leigh Griffiths and Michael Bowditch to shred the gnar in preparation  for South Australia’s first downhill skateboarding race, the Collingrove  Cup. This is a video of the shredding that took place during the week  before the race (which Jackson Shaperia won).</p>\n<p>Check out the <a href=\"https://www.skateboardracing.org.au/profiles/blogs/another-rad-week-in-radelaide\" target=\"_blank\">RACE RECAP</a> thanks to  the <a href=\"https://www.skateboardracing.org.au/\" target=\"_blank\">Australian Skateboard Racing Association</a>.</p>",
