    "pageTitle": "Upper Pro Teutonia 2014 with Scott and Max | MuirSkate Longboard Shop",
    "postDate": "2016-07-30",
    "author": "SkateHouseMedia",
    "bodyText": "<p><iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/057rnIZlAtc?showinfo=0\" width=\"700\" height=\"394\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\n<p>The Upper Pro Teutonia is one of the fastest and gnarliest skateboard races in the world. It’s rough, steep, and one of the wildest roller coaster you can ride. “Follow MuirSkate Team Riders Scott Lembach and Max Ballesteros as they charge down one of the fastest and gnarliest race tracks in the world with Brazilians Carlos Paixao and Bernardod Borges at the 2014 Upper Pro Teutonia! Congrats to Carlos Paixao on 1st in Open, Max for placing 2nd in Open, and Scott for placing 5th in Masters!” – <a href=\"https://www.muirskate.com\" target=\"_blank\">Muir Skate</a></p>\n<p>Drafting and passing at 70+mph is a whole new ballgame (especially when there is <a href=\"https://youtu.be/FBb4Y9mj5D8?t=19s\" target=\"_blank\">massive cracks</a> that you can hit when you pop out of the draft).</p>",
