    "pageTitle": "PDX: Sk8venger 2011 presented by Rip City Skate | SkateHouseMedia.com",
    "postDate": "2013-07-17",
    "author": "SkateHouseMedia",
    "bodyText": "<p><iframe width=\"700\" height=\"394\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/EuSGtd1FQU0\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"\"></iframe>\n</p><p>\n<a href=\"https://www.ripcityskate.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Rip City Skate</a>,  based out of Portland, Oregon has been a supporter of the  scene since day one with no plans of slowing down. Whether it is gear or an event,  Rip City will be sure that you are set to SKATE EVERYTHING. If you’re in the Portland area  be sure to stop by the shop to skate the GnarBowl or visit them online.</p>\n<p>“On July 23 2011, six teams, THE CUNT PUNTERS, RISK IT FOR A BISCUIT, 180, STEPDAD, BUTTHOLE SHRAPNEL, THE FOUR LOKOS,&nbsp; and JUST THE TIP competed for ultimate glory; They were the SK8VENGERS! made possible by an imaginary grant from the <a href=\"https://pdxdownhill.com/\" target=\"_blank\">PDXDOWNHILL.COM</a> foundation With special support from <a href=\"https://jonhueyphotography.com/\" target=\"_blank\">JON HUEY PHOTOGRAPHY</a> edited by yours truly, <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-W-fOJYC6sM\" target=\"_blank\">ADAM STOLTE</a> with music by YEASAYER <a href=\"https://skeetskeetbangbang.wordpress.com/\" target=\"_blank\">SKEETSKEETBANGBANG</a>!</p>\n<p>The Portland scene is heavily supported and backed by <a href=\"https://www.ripcityskate.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Rip City Skate</a>.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.skatehousemedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/Black-Friday-Flyer2.gif\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-3966\" title=\"Black-Friday-Flyer2\" src=\"https://www.skatehousemedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/Black-Friday-Flyer2.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"358\"></a></p>",
