    "pageTitle": "Sending It! at Redbull Steepcrest",
    "postDate": "2014-10-14",
    "author": "SkateHouseMedia",
    "bodyText": "<p><iframe src=\"//player.vimeo.com/video/112955079\" width=\"700\" height=\"394\" frameborder=\"0\" title=\"Sending It! at Redbull Steepcrest\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" allowfullscreen=\"\"></iframe></p>\n<p>Back on 2001, Redbull hosted the <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tgTQzbGwTnM\" target=\"_blank\">Streets of San Fransisco</a>. Flash forward 13 years and Redbull brings back the event for skateboarders and bikers to mash down. They went to one of the steepest hills in San Francisco and put small kickers across the lane for riders to battle it out in a race, best trick, and longest powerslide. Riders had 1 practice run and then sent to race. Many shenanigans were had when you spend the weekend with the <a href=\"https://www.skatehousemedia.com/08/29/2011/the-sunset-sliders-scramble\" target=\"_blank\">Sunset Sliders</a>.</p>",
