    "postDate": "2015-10-12",
    "author": "SkateHouseMedia",
    "bodyText": "<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"https://www.cometskateboards.com\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"https://www.skatehousemedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/12/comet.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\"></a>We’d like to give a huge shout out to the most recent Scene Supporter to come on board, <a href=\"https://www.cometskateboards.com\" target=\"_blank\">Comet Skateboards</a>.&nbsp; While the Comet name might be new around SkateHouseMedia, the company has been around for years and has always supported great riders and awesome events.&nbsp; Our good friend and Comet rider Anthony Flis visited the SkateHouse back in 2010 – <a href=\"https://www.skatehousemedia.com/04/06/2010/anthony-flis-visits\">be sure to check out the video from his stay</a>!</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><iframe width=\"700\" height=\"394\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/kPYEEh1DVz4?fs=1&amp;feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"\"></iframe><br>\nLiam Morgan and Anthony Flis shred around Ithaca, NY</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Comet takes pride in taking full advantage of environmentally friendly manufacturing techniques.&nbsp; “Our manufacturing decisions are guided by the concept of Cradle to  Cradle (C2C) as developed by William McDonough and Michael Braungart.  C2C eliminates the concept of waste through closed loop manufacturing,  which examines the entire life-cycle of all products and bi-products of  the system.”</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://www.skatehousemedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/12/comet-liambyron.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"544\"><br>\nByron Essert follows Liam Morgan with a beautiful backdrop.&nbsp; Photo by Blake Smith.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Stay tuned for big things to come from Comet and its riders through the end of 2011 and into 2012!</p>",
    "tags": [],
