    "pageTitle": "Skatesgiving – Pennsylvania | SkateHouseMedia.com",
    "postDate": "2016-01-16",
    "author": "SkateHouseMedia",
    "bodyText": "<p><iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/33730606\" width=\"700\" height=\"394\" frameborder=\"0\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" allowfullscreen=\"\"></iframe></p>\n<p>The first episode of Skatesgiving is here thanks to our friends at <a href=\"https://www.teamquebec.org\" target=\"_blank\">Team Quebec</a>!</p>\n<p>“Pennsylvania has a well-developed downhill scene with skaters of all  ages and events for all skill levels. Skatesgiving or not, Pennsylvania  is always on our list of places to go on the East Coast. In this week’s  episode of Skatesgiving the crew mob some runs near a little town by the  name of Lykens. Enjoy.”</p>\n<p>This trip wasn’t possible without the help from our awesome sponsors: <a href=\"https://www.cometskateboards.com/home/\" target=\"_blank\">Comet</a>, <a href=\"https://www.raynelongboards.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Rayne</a>, <a href=\"https://www.sector9.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Sector 9</a>, Kebbek, <a href=\"https://www.landyachtz.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Landyachtz</a> and <a href=\"https://www.rotulelongboards.com/en/\" target=\"_blank\">Rotule</a></p>",
