    "pageTitle": "Conner Stanek",
    "postDate": "December 15, 2015",
    "author": "SkateHouseMedia",
    "bodyText": "<p>Ashland Oregon born Conner Stanek has been exploring the Southern Oregon hills for ages. He was nice enough to be our guide for a few weeks and showed us some of the best runs they have to offer. With Conner we were testing some new radios that allow the rider to know precisely where oncoming traffic will be with the assistance of a lead car and in helmet radios. This allowed Conner to chop a few lanes and gain some extra speed. Still as the riders in <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UN6rqyfltRg\">Spain</a> know, radios are not always a perfect system.</p>",
