    "pageTitle": "East Coast Thanksgiving Shredfest",
    "postDate": "2011-07-05",
    "author": "SkateHouseMedia",
    "bodyText": "<p><iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/17979860\" width=\"700\" height=\"394\" frameborder=\"0\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" allowfullscreen=\"\"></iframe></p>\n<p>We know a lot of you are in school and thus unable to skate all day  every day or go on road trips to hit new spots. We feel your pain. Our  friends at <a href=\"https://www.kidsofthefutureskate.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Kids of the Future</a> are in the same situation. They decided to make good use of their  Thanksgiving break by skipping out on their families for a skate trip to  the mountains. Anthony Flis, Pat Schep, Keith Rebhorn, Dimitri Komarov,  and Ono Buono spent the whole week ripping the East Coast’s gnarliest  hills and sent in this video of their exploits.</p>",
